429, \"end\": 440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penny_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.893614404309004e-23, \"text\": \"Penny Smith\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penny_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penny_Smith\"}, {\"begin\": 445, \"end\": 454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9900913133448471, \"rank\": 0.010007260597930273, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the toast of Bookaar - population 159 - near Camperdown in Victoria's Western District, was overshadowed by Adriana Ruano Oliva's historic win.\", \"from\": 551, \"to\": 698, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 600, \"end\": 610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Camperdown\", \"score\": 0.9998035387618207, \"rank\": 0.0001686597586860527, \"text\": \"Camperdown\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Camperdown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Camperdown\"}, {\"begin\": 614, \"end\": 622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victoria_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9731855106353146, \"rank\": 0.01683720423970902, \"text\": \"Victoria\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victoria_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victoria_cricket_team\"}, {\"begin\": 663, \"end\": 670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adriana_La_Cerva\", \"score\": 0.9999999790370568, \"rank\": 2.0963031908823022e-08, \"text\": \"Adriana\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adriana_La_Cerva\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adriana_La_Cerva\"}, {\"begin\": 677, \"end\": 682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Oliva\", \"score\": 0.9997591070583707, \"rank\": 0.00016973676915415305, \"text\": \"Oliva\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Oliva\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Oliva\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ruano Oliva won Guatemala's first-ever Olympic gold medal, setting the Olympic record with her score of 45 out of 50 in the final.\", \"from\": 700, \"to\": 830, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 706, \"end\": 711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Oliva\", \"score\": 0.9997591070583707, \"rank\": 0.00016973676915415305, \"text\": \"Oliva\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Oliva\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Oliva\"}, {\"begin\": 716, \"end\": 725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guatemala\", \"score\": 0.9838512508554643, \"rank\": 0.016084167096810414, \"text\": \"Guatemala\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guatemala\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guatemala\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She finished five shots clear of Italian Maria Stanco.\", \"from\": 832, \"to\": 886, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 865, \"end\": 872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.7671002925160848, \"rank\": 0.3000012747167705, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 873, \"end\": 878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Duchess_Maria_Nikolaevna_of_Russia\", \"score\": 0.6314062607512959, \"rank\": 0.5797668512193148, \"text\": \"Maria\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Duchess_Maria_Nikolaevna_of_Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Duchess_Maria_Nikolaevna_of_Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nicknamed \\\"Pequena Gigante\\\" - Little Giant - Ruano Oliva is a former gymnast who retired from the sport in 2011 because of a spinal injury.\", \"from\": 888, \"to\": 1027, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She showed ample backbone in the final and was the only one of the six competitors to nail her first 15 shots.\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That gave Ruano Oliva a crucial buffer that she maintained to the end.\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1211, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1157, \"end\": 1162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Oliva\", \"score\": 0.9997591070583707, \"rank\": 0.00016973676915415305, \"text\": \"Oliva\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Oliva\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Oliva\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Guatemala had only won a silver and bronze before these Olympics.\", \"from\": 1213, \"to\": 1278, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1213, \"end\": 1222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guatemala\", \"score\": 0.9838512508554643, \"rank\": 0.016084167096810414, \"text\": \"Guatemala\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guatemala\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guatemala\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris is proving to be a medal rush for the South American country - on Tuesday, Jean Pierre Brol Cardenas won bronze in the men's trap.\", \"from\": 1280, \"to\": 1416, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1280, \"end\": 1285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999994229256, \"rank\": 5.77035009558737e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1330, \"end\": 1338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.8223681071946359, \"rank\": 0.2159952220671539, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1361, \"end\": 1377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_Pierre_Brol\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jean Pierre Brol\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_Pierre_Brol\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_Pierre_Brol\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ruano Oliva dedicated the gold medal to her late father, who died a month before the Tokyo Olympics, where she struggled and finished 26th..  \\\"Since then I have done a lot of work with a lot of love and this is dedicated to my angel, my family and to God,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1418, \"to\": 1684, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1424, \"end\": 1429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Oliva\", \"score\": 0.9997591070583707, \"rank\": 0.00016973676915415305, \"text\": \"Oliva\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Oliva\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Oliva\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Family also has had a major influence on Smith's sport - her mother Kim was at the 1984 Los Angeles Games as a groom for equestrian great Andrew Hoy, at the first of his eight Olympics.\", \"from\": 1686, \"to\": 1871, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1754, \"end\": 1757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 0.9999974134572567, \"rank\": 2.5211937828537205e-06, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\"}, {\"begin\": 1807, \"end\": 1817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.9999999713704715, \"rank\": 2.8176512718429855e-08, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}, {\"begin\": 1824, \"end\": 1834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Hoy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andrew Hoy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Hoy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Hoy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She said her father Michael was also shortlisted at one point for Olympic selection as a groom.\", \"from\": 1873, \"to\": 1968, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith was the typical sporty country kid, trying a wide range of pursuits, before family intervened and turned her towards trap shooting.\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 2107, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was only after my brother's motorcycling accident, when he took up shooting, that I got involved in the sport,\\\" Smith said.\", \"from\": 2109, \"to\": 2236, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You never know the places where life is going to lead you and I am really pleased now I have got an Olympic bronze medal.\\\"\", \"from\": 2238, \"to\": 2361, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Camperdown is also the birthplace of road time trial gold medallist Grace Brown.\", \"from\": 2363, \"to\": 2443, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2431, \"end\": 2442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murder_of_Grace_Brown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5887516897625905e-23, \"text\": \"Grace Brown\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murder_of_Grace_Brown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murder_of_Grace_Brown\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith, the 29-year-old left-hander, was steady in Wednesday's final for her first Olympic medal.\", \"from\": 2445, \"to\": 2541, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But two misses in her last elimination round left Smith one off the pace and she raised her arms to the crowd after scoring 32, five clear of fourth.\", \"from\": 2543, \"to\": 2692, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The world No.11 was sixth in the trap and mixed trap team at the Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 2694, \"to\": 2771, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier on Wednesday, Smith prevailed in a three-way shoot-off to make the final.\", \"from\": 2773, \"to\": 2854, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She joins Suzy Balogh (gold, 2004) and Catherine Skinner (gold, 2016) as Australian Olympic medallists in the women's trap.\", \"from\": 2856, \"to\": 2979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2866, \"end\": 2870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bae_Suzy\", \"score\": 0.9999999817914614, \"rank\": 1.195676785985392e-08, \"text\": \"Suzy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bae_Suzy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bae_Suzy\"}, {\"begin\": 2895, \"end\": 2912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catherine_Skinner\", \"score\": 0.9999945015598503, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Catherine Skinner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catherine_Skinner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catherine_Skinner\"}, {\"begin\": 2929, \"end\": 2939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9954636638524137, \"rank\": 0.004147080865939506, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Skinner also compete on Wednesday, but did not make it to the final.\", \"from\": 2981, \"to\": 3049, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The pressure told on Spain's world No.1 Fatima Galvez, who missed several shots early in the final and was the second of the six medal contenders to be eliminated.\", \"from\": 3051, \"to\": 3214, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3072, \"end\": 3077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"score\": 0.9999348037584842, \"rank\": 6.472984536946842e-05, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"dbpedia\": 